{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeVal\/toIso8601()"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeVal","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/TimeVal\/TimeValProtocol-Implementations"]]},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"symbolKind":"method","extendedModule":"GLib","title":"toIso8601()","platforms":[],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:4GLib15TimeValProtocolPAAE9toIso8601SSSgyF::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib7TimeValC","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"toIso8601"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"String","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"toIso8601"},{"text":"() -> ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"String"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"ISO 8601 allows a large number of date\/time formats, with or without"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"punctuation and optional elements. The format returned by this function","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"is a complete date and time, with optional punctuation included, the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"UTC time zone represented as “Z”, and the "},{"code":"tv_usec","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" part included if","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"and only if it is nonzero, i.e. either"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"“YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ” or “YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SS.fffffZ”.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This corresponds to the Internet date\/time format defined by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/www.ietf.org\/rfc\/rfc3339.txt"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and to either of the two most-precise formats defined by"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the W3C Note","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/TR\/NOTE-datetime-19980827","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Both of these documents are profiles of ISO 8601."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_date_time_format()"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_strdup_printf()"},{"type":"text","text":" if a different"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"variation of ISO 8601 format is required."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"code":"time","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" represents a date which is too large to fit into a ","type":"text"},{"code":"struct tm","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" will be returned. This is platform dependent. Note also that since","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTimeVal"},{"type":"text","text":" stores the number of seconds as a "},{"code":"glong","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", on 32-bit systems it"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is subject to the year 2038 problem. Accordingly, since GLib 2.62, this"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"function has been deprecated. Equivalent functionality is available using:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":null,"type":"codeListing","code":["G